<p>E. Helping Goals ( the “ends” desired example, it is write as to be achieved at the end of the helping relationship)</p>

<p>At the end of the working relationship, the worker and client will be able to:</p>

<p>1. Look for an alternative means of earning <br>2. Refer client for possible employment <br>3. Contact significant others that could temporarily assist the client in his or her current situation.</p>

<p>F. Action Plan (the “means” to achieve the defined goals, example specific interventions, activities, task that have to be done to achieve the goals) follow the format below:<br></p>
        <div contenteditable="true" class="plan" id="plan">
          <p>
            </p><p>Associated Problem 1: Insomnia<br>Interventions: </p>

<p>1. Practice good sleep hygiene: Establish a consistent sleep schedule, avoid electronics before bed, and create a relaxing sleep environment. </p>

<p>2. Consider cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT): CBT can help you identify and change thoughts and behaviors that keep you awake. </p>

<p>3. Explore supplemental options: Consult with a healthcare professional to discuss alternative supplements such as melatonin or magnesium to aid in quality sleep. </p>

<p>Activities:<br>- Establish a consistent sleep schedule by going to bed and waking up at the same time every day. </p>

<p>- Engage in regular physical activity during the day to feel more tired and mentally ready for sleep. </p>

<p>- Create a pre-sleep routine, such as reading or meditation, to calm your mind before bed. </p>

<p>Resources Needed: </p>

<p>- Appointment scheduling with a mental health professional specializing in CBT for insomnia assistance. </p>

<p>- Access to literature and resources that educate you about sleep hygiene and effective strategies. </p>

<p>Expected Outcome: </p>

<p>Experience faster and more sustained deep sleep throughout the night, resulting in improved energy and reduced stress throughout the day. </p>

<p>Associated Problem 2: Lack of Energy<br>Interventions: </p>

<p>1. Nutrition and dietary adjustments: Collaborate with a dietician to identify areas for nutritional improvement to boost energy. </p>

<p>2. Increase daily activity: In conjunction with an appropriate workout routine, incorporate regular exercise into your daily routine to boost energy levels. </p>

<p>3. Harness the power of "me" time: Create a balanced schedule that incorporates restorative activities like yoga, meditation, and socializing to enhance your overall well-being, which can provide more sustained energy throughout the day. </p>

<p>Activities: </p>

<p>- Cook more meals at home with a focus on balanced nutrition. </p>

<p>- Schedule workouts at the beginning of the day to maximize energy retention throughout the day. </p>

<p>- Dedicate 30 minutes daily to meditation, yoga, or socializing with friends to promote well-being and energy retention. </p>

<p>Resources Needed: </p>

<p>- In consultation with a dietician or nutritionist to pinpoint nutritional gaps and goals. </p>

<p>- Access to a gym or fitness facility, or resources to participate in at-home workout routines. </p>

<p>- Applications or materials to guide you through meditation, yoga, or other restorative activities. </p>

<p>Expected Outcome: </p>

<p>Feel more energized throughout the day, experience improved mood, and maintain increased productivity and motivation in your personal and professional life.</p>
          <p></p>
